            "answer_text": "Since g is inversely proportional to the square of the distance from the center of earth At R1 ( surface of earth) , g = g 1 At R2 , at a height H from the ground g = g1/ 4 g1 R1^2 = g2 R2^2 is a constant g1 R1^2 = g1 R2^2/ 4 R1 = R2/ 2 or R2 = 2 R1 R2 = R1 + H where H is the height from the surface R1 + H = 2 R1 H = R1 At a height equal to the radius of earth , the g will be one fourth of its value on the surface of earth ",
