            "answer_text": "Ans will be At the height equal to the radius of earth. g = GM/R^2 eq1 g'= GM/(R+H)^2 eq2 Where g' is gravitational acceleration at height H from surface of the earth Now divide the eq1 by eq2 g/g' = (R+H) ^2/ R^2 4/1 = (R+H) ^2/ R^2 2/1 = R+H/ R Now you can solve it further. It will be R= H At height R from surface of the earth gravitational acceleration will be 1/4 of the surface. R is the radius of earth. Hope you understand it. If you have any problem plz msg. ",
